node.text: Guys. Can we start a hiring chain by starting a sharing chain? I will do a live zoom call with two people who share this hiring chain post by @theofficialsting in their feed. Maybe you could offer to do a zoom call with one or two of your friends if they share in their feed as well. We’re all so starved for company in this pandemic. Someone in your feed would love to hang with you, i bet.  Let’s see how far we can get this post to go!! ❤️💛💙 @goodnews_movement @somegoodnews @coordown @tanksgoodnews

node.text: Let’s connect a little bit. -To be clear, because it seems it got muddy, I’ve always voted blue. I’m a Bernie girl and Biden/Harris has my vote. But I also know that polarization and externalizing human problems onto the “other side” doesn’t actually get us closer to fulfilling solutions. It’s time to listen to each other and try to understand and reflect so we can have real dialogue and walk into a brighter future together. And it’s time to start walking. The house is on fire. Let’s go, people. 🔥❤️

node.text: This is my Papa. He and I walked the Camino de Santiago two years ago. I feel so lucky to have had the chance to spend that time with him. He inspires me in so many ways it’s hard to count ‘em. He’s a dedicated social worker, a poet, a mystic and a wonderful father. Over the last decade he has walked every major route (and some not so major routes) of the Camino as a true pilgrim. He speaks 4 plus languages and often acts as a translator for other pilgrims on the road. I call him the “Old Man of the Camino”. And think pilgrims should get an extra gold stamp on their pilgrim passports if they find him. Wishing he and all the other great Dads out there a Happy Father’s Day.
